cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC. 

The paper presents a new data structure that is suitable for several applications, including database and networking applications. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The structure also has implications for networking (cs.NI) and security (cs.CR), as it is robust to certain standard errors. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for distributed implementations (cs.DC), which further supports the inclusion of this category.
